##Wuhan PNEUMONIA DOCTORS DICTATION: A major outbreak or coming

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

Oral | Xu Ping
By Wang Shan

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Oral | Xu Ping

By Wang Shan

From December 31,2019 to now, my hospital has more and more patients, for example, fever clinic, the current daily patient volume is more than 10 times the average hospital patient number, our hospital is still a little further from the city center. Winter itself is the flu season, prone to fever and respiratory tract infection. This group of patients includes influenza patients and common cold patients. Of course, some of them are COVID-19. However, many patients have not yet been tested. In the past, influenza, cold patients may go to respiratory or paediatric treatment, are now gathered in the fever clinic, so the flow of people is very large.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Outside the Hankou Railway Station

Today, hospitals are full to the hilt, and the capacity is stretched to the limit. As a hospital, our task is to diagnose and treat suspected patients, confirmed by the Wuhan Department of Disease Control. We all know the COVID-19 test already has a kit. These two days Wuhan Health System will test the authority delegated to the third-tier hospitals, that is, kits sent to the hospital. Some hospitals are not enough kits, some hospitals do not test conditions.

The COVID-19 is classified as a Class A infectious disease, and testing requires a dedicated laboratory. Even some top-three hospitals don't have labs like this, and it's too late to build them. First of all, it needs a negative pressure laboratory, air flow can only enter and can not leave; the laboratory cleanliness, ventilation system, sterilization have high requirements. If you do not have the conditions to do the test, there is likely to be a virus leakage, the laboratory became a source of pollution, the hospital was also contaminated, it is terrible.

There's a lot to think about when you think about how health systems respond to COVID-19. In fact, at first, the whole situation was manageable. When the new virus first appeared in Wuhan, it was detected by the Wuhan Health System itself. On December 31,2019, the Wuhan Health and Health Commission reported that 27 cases of infection were found. At that time, no one knew what this new type of pneumonia was. When they found out, they put these patients under strict quarantine. On Jan. 9, experts identified the virus, and two days later, its genome was sequenced. This is very rapid in terms of response. It is not easy to identify a new form of pneumonia in the midst of a severe influenza pandemic in Wuhan, with more than 20 cases in a population of more than 11m. That's where you need to be sure.

The problem comes later. After 27 cases appeared, the Wuhan Health System adopted the policy of internal tightening and external loosening. "tight" is the timely detection of cases, and made strict isolation and response. "loose" is not a large-scale public notice of the community, let everyone alert to the disease, there is no call to wear masks. This time, the system is not aware of the control nature of the infectious disease, without social support, it is very difficult.

What does social support include? The first is to call on the public to stop large-scale Movement of people, do not have large-scale meetings, wearing masks, washing hands and these also need to be reminded. Dealing with COVID-19 is not something the health system can do on its own. If you think about it, people don't realize how important it is, how serious it is, and then they let their guard down, and then there's the 40,000-person Seder. This lack of awareness will continue until the onset of the state, that is, people are sick, but the other party does not feel serious, will not come to the hospital.

The Baibu Pavilion Community in Wuhan is home to 40,000 people during the Lunar New Year holiday in southern China (photo provided by China News Service) 

It also has to do with the characteristics of the disease. The target of the COVID-19 attack is the Angiotensin-converting enzyme. This stuff is abundant in the lungs. Therefore, the initial symptoms of the infected person are not very serious. We know that people with influenza have fever, runny nose, dry cough, and expectoration. People infected with COVID-19 may initially have no energy, a dry cough or a low grade fever, or even a slightly higher than normal body temperature, which can not be measured. Some are still in the incubation period, there is no performance. COVID-19 is similar to SARS in some ways, but its symptoms appear to be less severe than SARS, so it is ignored. But just because it's not serious doesn't mean it's not contagious.

It now appears that this could be the key to the spread of the epidemic. The difference between COVID-19 and SARS is precisely why it spread so quickly. The sudden increase in the number of follow-up patients is related to patients with less severe illness or to patients with latent virus. The patients we identified in the first wave had a market infection, but in the second wave, the patients had no connection to the market. So, if at first, the patient's symptoms are severe, and the virus mutates quickly, people may have a different attitude when it comes to coping. In retrospect, the virus is even more elusive than SARS, it is erratic, in some patients with very mild symptoms, and if the patient is not hospitalized, continue to spread, he may spread people with very serious symptoms.

To some extent, this careless response has something to do with the fact that Wuhan did not suffer from SARS. In 2003, SARS cases in Wuhan were few and had little impact. You See, Beijing and Hong Kong, when SARS was so serious, this time they took it very seriously. When I first started talking to my doctor friends around me, they weren't too concerned about it either.

My hospital's respiratory clinic, starting December 31, is actually doing a higher level of protection. But the other departments of our hospital, objectively speaking, at that time the protection force is not in place. Some patients come in because of other symptoms, the condition is also in the incubation period, it can not be seen that he has a problem, in the course of contact, there has been an infection of health care workers. After that, our hospital took very strict precautions. Even the back office, they wear masks, take their temperature every day, for protection.

I am from Wuhan, but I have a deep impression on SARS. I was studying in Beijing at the time, and our school was closed for three months. It's forbidden to move around in the school. We each issued a card, to eat in this canteen, can not go to another canteen, between the dormitory can not visit, all in order to prevent infection. At that time, I saw a lot of information about SARS on the Internet, feel very terrible. This virus came, I was anxious from the beginning, I persuaded my family, they still do not care very much. Two days ago, the Expert Group of National Health Commission was not infected? He was well protected, but he went down anyway. This makes my family, including the community began to pay attention to it, think it is a matter, to pay attention to.

Medical staff wearing protective clothing for treatment (photo provided by China News Service)

January 10,2020, is the same day in Wuhan, or in any hospital. Before this, contact with the south China market and the incidence of patients have been done quarantine response measures. Unexpectedly, the potential infectors began to get sick again and again. On January 20, more than 100 new cases were reported in Wuhan within two days. It was actually the potential infectors who infected the New People. In our view, this time period represents the arrival of a second wave of eruptions. At this time, we said the test method has come out. But some hospitals, even if there are reagents, can not hold so many patients, only for serious patients priority for diagnostic testing, mild first do not test, let them go home.

This is different from the response that followed SARS. At that time, even without testing, doctors could isolate suspected cases based on the patient's epidemiological history and symptoms. That didn't happen this time, and a lot of people with suspected symptoms went home. Some hospitals have been receiving complaints from patients. Said the hospital wasn't treating him. But in fact, this patient first went to a hospital, he saw a large number of people, they switched to another hospital, the results of the queue is also long, then switch hospitals. Now the fever clinic in the hospital, the outpatient department of aspiration, the basic need to queue for four or five hours. Such patients, if later diagnosed with the new form of pneumonia, are likely to infect more people. Public transportation to and from the hospital is also a big risk. I have to say, we don't know enough about disease.

From yesterday, the Health Department decided to focus on the treatment of fever patients in designated hospitals, which is a good method. Like Xiaotangshan in Beijing before, it can prevent the flow of patients, and I hope to see good results. In fact, if you look at the law, SARS in 2003 and now the emergence of the COVID-19, are the emergence of large transport node cities, population density. Wuhan's two worst affected districts are also extremely densely populated, with ten thousand people per square kilometer.

The spread of the virus has a lot to do with population density. We don't think the big break is here yet. The most dangerous time is after the Spring Festival, people return to work, people to the first-tier cities, to a more densely populated areas. These days we all see the expert's call, "can not go to Wuhan, Wuhan people can not come out, not out. ". In fact, at the beginning, we heard rumors that the entire city of Wuhan would be blockaded, but today we did not expect it to be so.

In Our own judgment, the spread of COVID-19 May continue until May, based on the fact that, on the one hand, prevention and control measures are keeping up, and on the other hand, COVID-19 is afraid of the heat, and when the weather warms up, can also work on viruses. We are now mentally prepared for May Day. At this time, I want to say, as Wuhan People, our hometown is here, the cause is here, we want to protect the city.

(Xu Ping is an alias)
